author: julianfoad
msg: In svnserve: don't hide fatal errors in inetd and tunnel modes.
For example: "echo foo | svnserve -t" previously exited successfully, but now
gives "svnserve: E210004: Malformed network data" on stderr and exit code 1.
(sub_main): On any fatal error after starting a connection in inetd or
tunnel mode, report it and exit non-zero instead of exiting silently
